name: Suharti Fried Chicken
address: Jl. Cokroaminoto, Ubung, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80116, Indonesia
review 1: The real definition of "ada harga ada kualitas dan rasa". The chicken seasoning is super savory and delicious.  The chicken is also very tender, easy to chew, so even if it is consumed by children, they will easily swallow it.  The dining area is spacious with an open-air model, so the air circulation is excellent.  The service is also friendly.  BTW the serving time is surprisingly quite short and the chicken gets to the table warm.  In my opinion, the price of drinks here is relatively expensive when compared to other places.  The parking lot is not that wide, I guess it's only about 4 cars. Beside fried chicken, they offer another Indonesian menu, such as gudeg, karedok, sayur asem, etc.
review 2: Authentic fried chicken, sambal taste good and the chicken so tender. One of the oldest fried chicken from central of Java
review 3: Place's a bit old, but the chicken tastes great especially with the kremesan. Parking space is big enough for some cars, and the place is kept clean.
review 4: One of my fav chicken. Tho it‚Äôs good, I feel like it‚Äôs a bit expensive somehow. Service is okay ‚Äî staff is a little cold but serving time is fast.
review 5: Chicken very tender and tasty. Originally they are from Yogyakarta

name: Bakso Bakwan Bintang
address: Jl. Angsoka Cargo Permai No.3A blok C, Ubung, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1:
Bakso Bakwan Bintang serves some of the tastiest bakso I've had in Bali. It's undoubtedly the best bakso experience I've had on the island. The flavors were rich, and the dish was incredibly satisfying.

However, it's important to note that, like many other food stalls, managing expectations regarding the service is crucial. While the food is top-notch, the service might not align with traditional restaurant standards. It's more of a grab-and-go setup.

If you're someone who prioritizes exceptional taste over formal service, this is the place for you. Just be prepared for a no-frills experience but an absolute treat for your taste buds
review 2: Good taste, big enough space . Need more table due always full of customers, the place is clean enough, the parking area is quite big but for motorbike only,  the car must find its own parking along the side of the road.
